1) terminals give  
[1,1]={NT18, NT58, NT65}  (all → ‘t115’)  
[2,2]={NT18}             (→ ‘t164’)  
[3,3]={NT2, NT66}        (→ ‘t73’)  
[4,4]={NT59, NT63}       (→ ‘t31’)

2) span (1,2): from NT18 NT18 → NT64, so [1,2]={NT64}.

3) span (3,4): from NT2 NT63 → NT53, so [3,4]={NT53}.

4) finally S → NT64 NT53 and NT64∈[1,2], NT53∈[3,4], so S covers the whole string.

Hence the grammar does generate “t115 t164 t73 t31”.
